WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.040
Spray the crust, and it does not harden all at once. Each binder sets on

2
00:00:04.140 --> 00:00:07.606
its own clock — and that turns out to be a feature, not a bug.

3
00:00:09.200 --> 00:00:11.914
Alginate gels in minutes — instant early grip.

4
00:00:12.014 --> 00:00:14.851
Gamma-P-G-A firms up over hours. And the calcite

5
00:00:14.951 --> 00:00:18.216
slowly ripens across the full thirty-two-hour protocol.

6
00:00:20.900 --> 00:00:24.115
So the fast polymers carry the crust through its fragile first

7
00:00:24.215 --> 00:00:27.591
day, while the durable calcite takes over as the long-term floor.

8
00:00:27.666 --> 00:00:30.106
Then months of sun and wind slowly wear even the

9
00:00:30.206 --> 00:00:33.176
calcite down. Because that floor lasts longest, it is what

10
00:00:33.276 --> 00:00:35.769
sets how long you can wait before spraying again.

